         <abstract>
            <p>Let Δ&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(a, b) = (ba&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; + (a - 1)/b)&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + 4a&lt;sup&gt;n&lt;/sup&gt; with n ≥ 1 and b ∣ a - 1. If L is a finite set of primes such that for each n ≥ 1 there exists some q ∈ L for which the Legendre symbol (Δ&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(a, b)/q) ≠ -1, we call L a quadratic residue cover (QRC) for the quadratic fields &lt;tex-math&gt;$K_n(a, b) = Q(\sqrt{\Delta_n(a, b))}$&lt;/tex-math&gt;. It is shown how the existence of a QRC for any a, b can be used to determine lower bounds on the class number of K&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(a, b) when Δ&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(a, b) is the discriminant of K&lt;sub&gt;n&lt;/sub&gt;(a, b). Also, QRCs are computed for all 1 ≤ a, b ≤ 10000.</p>
          </abstract>
